<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 22 at 2:26PM CDT  by NWS Memphis</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Calhoun
County through 300 PM CDT...
At 225 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Slate Springs, or 20 miles west of Houston, moving northeast at 10
mph.
HAZARD...Half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Calhoun City, Vardaman, Derma, Pittsboro, Slate Springs and Slate
Spring.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
